1
00:00:01,720 --> 00:00:04,320
Space, 1969.

2
00:00:06,640 --> 00:00:07,640
No!

3
00:00:08,600 --> 00:00:11,040
The Doctor we saw on the beach
is a future version,

4
00:00:11,120 --> 00:00:13,080
200 years older than the one up there.

5
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:16,440
DOCTOR: Canton Everett Delaware III.
Who's he?

6
00:00:17,200 --> 00:00:18,760
What the hell is that?

7
00:00:18,840 --> 00:00:20,520
Mr President...

8
00:00:22,640 --> 00:00:25,120
You didn't have to kill her,
she couldn't even remember you!

9
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:26,320
How does that work?

10
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:28,760
We can only remember you
while we're seeing you, is that it?

11
00:00:29,760 --> 00:00:30,760
(GASPS)

12
00:00:31,600 --> 00:00:33,000
Canton! Are you okay?

13
00:00:33,080 --> 00:00:34,720
Doctor, I'm pregnant.

14
00:00:39,560 --> 00:00:41,080
No!

15
00:00:41,160 --> 00:00:42,160
(SCREAMING)

16
00:00:42,320 --> 00:00:43,600
(PANTING)

17
00:00:47,160 --> 00:00:48,760
Suspect directly ahead.

18
00:00:48,840 --> 00:00:50,400
Coming to you now. Over.

19
00:00:56,080 --> 00:00:57,360
(PANTING)

20
00:01:09,920 --> 00:01:11,360
(CRIES OUT)

21
00:01:22,560 --> 00:01:24,280
-Canton.
-Miss Pond.

22
00:01:28,080 --> 00:01:30,480
-Is that a body bag?
-Yes, it is.

23
00:01:30,560 --> 00:01:32,720
-It's empty.
-How about that?

24
00:01:33,400 --> 00:01:35,840
Do you even know
why you're doing this, hey?

25
00:01:36,560 --> 00:01:38,400
Can you even remember?

26
00:01:38,880 --> 00:01:39,920
The warehouse?

27
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:42,320
It's that monster. Amy! Amy!

28
00:01:44,120 --> 00:01:46,120
(INAUDIBLE SHOUTING)

29
00:01:46,200 --> 00:01:48,480
-What the hell's going on?
-Look behind you.

30
00:01:48,560 --> 00:01:50,040
There's nothing behind me!

31
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:52,280
-(SCREAMING)
-Look! Canton, look!

32
00:01:52,360 --> 00:01:53,920
ALIEN: Canton.

33
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:55,240
(GUNSHOT)

34
00:02:03,160 --> 00:02:06,840
MAN ON PA: All visitors
to remain behind the yellow line.

35
00:02:06,920 --> 00:02:10,160
All visitors to remain behind
the yellow line.

36
00:02:10,240 --> 00:02:11,840
We found Amy Pond.

37
00:02:11,920 --> 00:02:15,760
She had strange markings on her arm.

38
00:02:17,640 --> 00:02:19,040
Do you know what they are?

39
00:02:21,680 --> 00:02:23,520
Why don't you ask her?

40
00:02:31,840 --> 00:02:32,840
(SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE)

41
00:02:48,520 --> 00:02:50,280
(METALLIC CLATTER)

42
00:02:55,760 --> 00:02:56,760
(CHITTERING)

43
00:02:57,680 --> 00:02:59,000
I see you.

44
00:03:01,160 --> 00:03:03,200
I see you!

45
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:09,240
-Dr Song.
-(GASPS)

46
00:03:09,760 --> 00:03:11,320
Dr Song!

47
00:03:17,080 --> 00:03:18,560
Go, go, go!

48
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:22,080
Don't move!

49
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:30,080
-It's over.
-They're here, Canton.

50
00:03:30,160 --> 00:03:32,280
-They're everywhere.
-I know.

51
00:03:32,360 --> 00:03:35,880
-America's being invaded.
-You were invaded a long time ago.

52
00:03:35,960 --> 00:03:37,800
America is occupied.

53
00:03:37,880 --> 00:03:41,720
You're coming with us, Dr Song.
There's no way out this time.

54
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:45,720
There's always a way out.

55
00:03:56,240 --> 00:03:57,880
We found Dr Song.

56
00:03:58,480 --> 00:04:00,480
These bricks, what are they made of?

57
00:04:01,240 --> 00:04:03,080
-Where is she?
-She ran.

58
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:05,720
Off the 50th floor.

59
00:04:08,240 --> 00:04:10,880
I'd say zero-balanced dwarf star alloy.

60
00:04:11,880 --> 00:04:15,000
The densest material in the universe.
Nothing gets through that.

61
00:04:16,320 --> 00:04:18,520
You're building me the perfect prison.

62
00:04:22,680 --> 00:04:24,880
And it still won't be enough.

63
00:04:40,640 --> 00:04:43,160
-What are you waiting for?
-I'm waiting for you to run.

64
00:04:43,240 --> 00:04:45,280
It'd look better if I shot you
while you were running.

65
00:04:45,360 --> 00:04:48,440
Then again, looks aren't everything.

66
00:04:49,840 --> 00:04:51,040
(GUNSHOT)

67
00:04:56,480 --> 00:04:58,640
Is there a reason you're doing this?

68
00:04:58,720 --> 00:05:02,160
I want you to know where you stand.
In a cell.

69
00:05:02,240 --> 00:05:05,440
In a perfect cell.
Nothing can penetrate these walls.

70
00:05:05,520 --> 00:05:08,080
Not a sound, not a radio wave.

71
00:05:11,760 --> 00:05:13,960
Not the tiniest particle of anything.

72
00:05:14,040 --> 00:05:17,600
In here, you are literally cut off
from the rest of the universe.

73
00:05:18,920 --> 00:05:21,000
(CHATTERING, INDISTINCT)

74
00:05:23,520 --> 00:05:25,240
So I guess they can't hear us, right?

75
00:05:25,320 --> 00:05:27,680
-Good work, Canton. Door sealed?
-You bet.

76
00:05:28,840 --> 00:05:31,200
(BOTH GASPING)

77
00:05:33,760 --> 00:05:35,640
-You okay?
-Finally.

78
00:05:35,720 --> 00:05:38,120
These things
could really do with air holes.

79
00:05:38,200 --> 00:05:39,440
Never had a complaint before.

80
00:05:39,520 --> 00:05:41,440
Isn't it going to look odd that
you're staying in here with us?

81
00:05:41,520 --> 00:05:42,680
Odd, but not alarming.

82
00:05:42,760 --> 00:05:43,800
They know
there's no way out of this place.

83
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:46,000
Exactly. Whatever they might think
we're doing in here,

84
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:48,520
they know we're not going anywhere.

85
00:05:52,240 --> 00:05:53,520
Shall we?

86
00:05:54,680 --> 00:05:56,040
What about Dr Song?

87
00:05:56,120 --> 00:05:58,800
-She dove off a rooftop!
-Don't worry. She does that.

88
00:05:58,880 --> 00:06:02,160
Amy, Rory,
open all the doors to the swimming pool.

89
00:06:09,520 --> 00:06:10,680
So, we know they're everywhere.

90
00:06:10,760 --> 00:06:12,800
Not just a landing party,
an occupying force.

91
00:06:12,880 --> 00:06:15,240
And they've been here
a very, very long time.

92
00:06:15,320 --> 00:06:17,320
But nobody knows that,
"cause no one can remember them.

93
00:06:17,400 --> 00:06:18,560
-So what are they up to?
-No idea.

94
00:06:18,640 --> 00:06:22,560
But the good news is...
we've got a secret weapon.

95
00:06:28,520 --> 00:06:30,280
Apollo 71'syour secret weapon?

96
00:06:30,360 --> 00:06:33,960
No, no, it's not Apollo 71,
that would be silly.

97
00:06:34,920 --> 00:06:37,160
It's Neil Armstrong's foot.

98
00:06:37,320 --> 00:06:39,520
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

99
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:23,960
RADIO NEWSREADER: In just a few days
mankind will set foot on the moon

100
00:07:24,040 --> 00:07:25,680
for the first time.

101
00:07:25,760 --> 00:07:29,520
Today the President reaffirmed
America's commitment...

102
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:30,600
(RADIO OFF)

103
00:07:30,840 --> 00:07:32,760
Ready. Check.

104
00:07:32,840 --> 00:07:35,520
-Clear.
-Clear.

105
00:07:40,520 --> 00:07:42,200
-Ow!
-Ha! So, three months.

106
00:07:42,280 --> 00:07:45,040
-What have we found out?
-Well, they are everywhere.

107
00:07:45,120 --> 00:07:48,960
-Every state in America. Ow!
-Not just America, the entire world.

108
00:07:49,040 --> 00:07:51,560
There's a greater concentration
here, though.

109
00:07:51,640 --> 00:07:52,680
Ow!

110
00:07:53,440 --> 00:07:54,640
You okay?

111
00:07:56,640 --> 00:07:58,880
-All better.
-Better?

112
00:07:58,960 --> 00:08:01,680
Turns out I was wrong.
I'm... I'm not pregnant.

113
00:08:03,200 --> 00:08:05,080
-What's up?
-Nothing.

114
00:08:05,160 --> 00:08:07,120
(CHUCKLES) Really, nothing, seriously.

115
00:08:07,200 --> 00:08:09,600
So you've seen them,
but you don't remember them.

116
00:08:09,680 --> 00:08:13,480
You've seen them, too.
That night at the warehouse, remember?

117
00:08:13,560 --> 00:08:15,200
While you were pretending
to hunt us down,

118
00:08:15,280 --> 00:08:18,480
we saw hundreds of those things.
We still don't know what they look like.

119
00:08:18,560 --> 00:08:21,040
It's like they edit themselves
out of your memory

120
00:08:21,120 --> 00:08:22,200
as soon as you look away.

121
00:08:22,280 --> 00:08:25,040
The exact second you're not looking
at them, you can't remember anything.

122
00:08:25,120 --> 00:08:27,520
Sometimes you feel a bit sick, though,
but not always.

123
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:29,040
So that's why you marked your skin?

124
00:08:29,120 --> 00:08:31,000
Only way we'd know
if we'd had an encounter.

125
00:08:31,080 --> 00:08:32,080
How long have they been here?

126
00:08:32,160 --> 00:08:34,880
That's what we've spent the last
three months trying to find out.

127
00:08:34,960 --> 00:08:37,480
Not easy, if you can't remember
anything you discover.

128
00:08:37,560 --> 00:08:38,560
But how long do you think?

129
00:08:38,640 --> 00:08:40,440
As long as there's been something
in the corner of your eye

130
00:08:40,520 --> 00:08:42,840
or creaking in your house
or breathing under your bed

131
00:08:42,920 --> 00:08:44,920
or voices through a wall.

132
00:08:46,840 --> 00:08:48,600
They've been running your lives
for a very long time now,

133
00:08:48,680 --> 00:08:53,560
so keep this straight in your head.
We are not fighting an alien invasion.

134
00:08:55,920 --> 00:09:00,480
We're leading a revolution.
And today the battle begins.

135
00:09:00,560 --> 00:09:02,200
-How?
-Like this.

136
00:09:03,640 --> 00:09:04,960
-Ow!
-(LAUGHS)

137
00:09:05,840 --> 00:09:10,000
Nano recorder.
Fuses with the cartilage in your hand.

138
00:09:11,200 --> 00:09:14,160
Ow! Then it tunes itself directly
to the speech centres in your brain.

139
00:09:14,240 --> 00:09:16,960
It'll pick up your voice,
no matter what. Telepathic connection.

140
00:09:17,040 --> 00:09:21,480
So, the moment you see
one of the creatures, you activate it

141
00:09:22,360 --> 00:09:24,560
and describe aloud
exactly what you're seeing.

142
00:09:26,480 --> 00:09:28,280
DOCTOR: And describe aloud
exactly what you're seeing.

143
00:09:28,360 --> 00:09:31,680
Because the moment you break contact,
you're going to forget it happened.

144
00:09:31,760 --> 00:09:33,920
The light will flash if
you've left yourself a message.

145
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:36,520
You keep checking your hand.

146
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:38,720
If you've had an encounter,
that's the first you'll know about it.

147
00:09:38,800 --> 00:09:40,240
Why didn't you tell me this
before we started?

148
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:43,920
I did. But even information about
these creatures erases itself over time.

149
00:09:45,880 --> 00:09:47,520
I couldn't refresh it
'cause I couldn't talk to you.

150
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:48,600
(THUDDING)

151
00:09:53,800 --> 00:09:54,920
What?

152
00:09:56,680 --> 00:09:58,920
-What are you staring at?
-Look at your hand.

153
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:03,240
Why's it doing that?

154
00:10:03,320 --> 00:10:06,160
What does it mean if the light's
flashing? What did I just tell you?

155
00:10:06,240 --> 00:10:08,160
-I haven't...
-Play it.

156
00:10:12,120 --> 00:10:14,280
CANTON: My God, how did it get in here?

157
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:17,960
DOCTOR: Keep eye contact with
the creature and when I say,

158
00:10:18,040 --> 00:10:22,040
turn back, and when you do,
straighten my bow tie.

159
00:10:22,560 --> 00:10:24,680
CANTON: What? What are you staring at?

160
00:10:24,760 --> 00:10:26,520
RIVER: Look at your hand.

161
00:10:30,360 --> 00:10:33,160
It's a hologram, extrapolated
from the photo on Amy's phone.

162
00:10:33,240 --> 00:10:35,080
Take a good long look.

163
00:10:36,360 --> 00:10:38,880
You just saw an image
of one of the creatures we're fighting.

164
00:10:38,960 --> 00:10:40,840
Describe it to me.

165
00:10:40,920 --> 00:10:42,560
-I can't.
-No.

166
00:10:44,080 --> 00:10:45,560
Neither can I.

167
00:10:46,520 --> 00:10:49,280
You straightened my bow tie
because I planted the idea in your head

168
00:10:49,360 --> 00:10:51,720
-while you were looking at the creature.
-So they could do that to people.

169
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:53,920
You could be doing stuff and
not really knowing why you're doing it.

170
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:55,880
Like post-hypnotic suggestion.

171
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:58,000
Ruling the world
with post-hypnotic suggestion?

172
00:10:58,080 --> 00:10:59,560
Now then, a little girl in a space suit.

173
00:10:59,640 --> 00:11:01,440
They got the suit from NASA,
but where did they get the girl?

174
00:11:01,520 --> 00:11:02,720
-Could be anywhere.
-Except they probably stayed

175
00:11:02,800 --> 00:11:05,120
close to that warehouse,
"cause why bother doing anything else?

176
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:06,640
And they take her from somewhere

177
00:11:06,760 --> 00:11:08,920
that will cause
the least amount of attention.

178
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:11,320
But you'll have to find her.
I'm off to NASA.

179
00:11:11,400 --> 00:11:13,560
CANTON: Find her? Where do we look?

180
00:11:15,240 --> 00:11:16,680
Children's homes.

181
00:11:17,800 --> 00:11:19,000
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

182
00:11:19,400 --> 00:11:21,280
-Hello?
-FBI.

183
00:11:21,360 --> 00:11:23,200
You must be Dr Renfrew. Can we come in?

184
00:11:23,280 --> 00:11:26,280
-The children are asleep.
-We'll be very quiet.

185
00:11:26,360 --> 00:11:28,920
Is there a problem?

186
00:11:29,520 --> 00:11:31,720
-It's about a missing child.
-Well, what are you...

187
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:35,240
Yes, yes, come in, please.

188
00:11:39,080 --> 00:11:40,480
This way.

189
00:11:41,400 --> 00:11:45,560
Please excuse the writing. It...
(CHUCKLES) ...keeps happening.

190
00:11:45,640 --> 00:11:48,320
I try to clean it up.

191
00:11:51,720 --> 00:11:55,160
-It's the kids, yeah? They do that?
-Yes. The children.

192
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:57,840
It must be, yes.

193
00:12:00,760 --> 00:12:04,800
Anyway, my office is this way.

194
00:12:10,040 --> 00:12:12,360
We nearly didn't come to this place.

195
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:16,120
I understood Graystark Hall
was closed in '67.

196
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:19,760
-That's the plan, yes.
-The plan?

197
00:12:19,840 --> 00:12:22,400
-Not long now.
-It's 1969.

198
00:12:22,480 --> 00:12:26,400
Uh, no, no. We close in '67.
That's the plan, yes.

199
00:12:26,480 --> 00:12:28,040
You misunderstood me, sir.

200
00:12:28,120 --> 00:12:30,360
It's 1969 now.

201
00:12:30,440 --> 00:12:32,440
Why are you saying that?
Of course it isn't.

202
00:12:32,560 --> 00:12:33,680
July.

203
00:12:36,920 --> 00:12:39,760
(MUMBLING) My office is this way,
this way.

204
00:12:43,840 --> 00:12:46,120
-I'll check upstairs.
-Be careful.

205
00:13:14,240 --> 00:13:17,480
-(MOBILE BLEEPS)
-Amy?

206
00:13:17,840 --> 00:13:19,760
I think we've found the place
she was taken from.

207
00:13:19,840 --> 00:13:21,640
-How do you know?
-'Cause those things have been here.

208
00:13:21,720 --> 00:13:23,040
But the whole place is deserted.

209
00:13:23,120 --> 00:13:25,520
There's just one guy here
and I think he's lost it.

210
00:13:25,600 --> 00:13:27,360
Repeated memory wipes
fry your head eventually.

211
00:13:27,440 --> 00:13:29,840
Find out what you can
but don't hang around.

212
00:13:29,920 --> 00:13:30,920
Where are you?

213
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:33,080
Gotta go. Got company.

214
00:13:33,800 --> 00:13:36,480
Don't worry. I put everything
back the way I found out.

215
00:13:36,560 --> 00:13:40,000
Oh, except this. There's always a bit
left over, isn't there?

216
00:13:49,080 --> 00:13:50,440
(STEADY BEEPING)

217
00:13:56,960 --> 00:13:58,200
(GASPS)

218
00:14:13,200 --> 00:14:17,080
AMY: I can see them, but I think
they're asleep. Get out! Just get out!

219
00:14:33,720 --> 00:14:34,800
(GASPS)

220
00:14:46,280 --> 00:14:47,280
(CHITTERING QUIETLY)

221
00:15:04,160 --> 00:15:05,720
(BIN CLATTERS, ALIEN CHITTERING)

222
00:15:12,440 --> 00:15:13,680
(SIGHS)

223
00:15:23,600 --> 00:15:25,080
Now, one more time, sir.

224
00:15:25,160 --> 00:15:27,200
How the hell did you get
into the command module?

225
00:15:27,280 --> 00:15:28,400
I told you!

226
00:15:28,480 --> 00:15:31,760
I'm on a top-secret mission
for the President.

227
00:15:32,600 --> 00:15:35,920
Well, maybe if you'd just get President
Nixon to assure us of that, sir,

228
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:37,760
that would be swell.

229
00:15:38,920 --> 00:15:40,720
I sent him a message.

230
00:15:41,880 --> 00:15:43,160
(CLEARING THROAT)

231
00:15:44,320 --> 00:15:48,200
Hello. I believe it's Mr Gardner,
is that correct? Head of security?

232
00:15:48,280 --> 00:15:50,160
Ah, yes, sir. Yes, Mr President.

233
00:15:50,240 --> 00:15:52,720
-Mr Grant, is it?
-Yes, Mr President.

234
00:15:53,240 --> 00:15:56,360
The hopes and dreams of millions
of Americans stand here today,

235
00:15:56,440 --> 00:15:59,640
at Cape Kennedy, and you're
the men who guard those dreams.

236
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:02,800
On behalf of the American people,
I thank you.

237
00:16:02,880 --> 00:16:04,120
You're welcome, Mr President.

238
00:16:04,200 --> 00:16:06,440
I understand you have a baby on the way,
Mr Grant?

239
00:16:06,520 --> 00:16:07,520
Yes, Mr President.

240
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:09,880
What are you hoping for,
a boy or a girl?

241
00:16:09,960 --> 00:16:11,600
-Just a healthy American, sir.
-(CHUCKLES)

242
00:16:11,680 --> 00:16:15,080
A healthy American will do just nicely.
(CHUCKLING)

243
00:16:15,160 --> 00:16:17,640
Now, fellas, listen. This man here,

244
00:16:17,760 --> 00:16:21,160
code name The Doctor, is doing
some work for me personally.

245
00:16:21,640 --> 00:16:23,920
Could you, uh, cut him a little slack?

246
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:27,040
Er, Mr President,
he did break into Apollo 71.

247
00:16:30,200 --> 00:16:34,080
Well, I'm sure he had
a very good reason for that. (CHUCKLES)

248
00:16:34,160 --> 00:16:36,400
Uh, but I need you to release him now,
so he can get on

249
00:16:36,480 --> 00:16:38,920
with some very important work
for the American people.

250
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:41,800
-Could you do that for me?
-Well...

251
00:16:41,880 --> 00:16:44,800
Son, I am your Commander in Chief.

252
00:16:44,880 --> 00:16:47,480
Uh, then I guess that would be fine,
Mr President.

253
00:16:47,560 --> 00:16:49,160
Glad to hear it.

254
00:16:52,640 --> 00:16:55,440
Thank you! Bye-bye.

255
00:16:59,320 --> 00:17:01,080
Carry on, gentlemen.

256
00:17:10,480 --> 00:17:12,680
(CLEARS THROAT) America salutes you.

257
00:17:26,440 --> 00:17:30,840
This place, it's been closed for years.
What have you been doing?

258
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:34,480
Oh, the child,

259
00:17:35,280 --> 00:17:37,560
she must be cared for.

260
00:17:37,640 --> 00:17:39,160
It's important.

261
00:17:39,760 --> 00:17:41,120
That's what they said.

262
00:17:42,040 --> 00:17:43,200
That's what who said?

263
00:17:52,040 --> 00:17:53,360
(DOOR OPENS, AMY GASPS)

264
00:17:57,400 --> 00:17:59,560
Hello. Who are you?

265
00:18:00,600 --> 00:18:02,920
No, I think she's just dreaming.

266
00:18:16,960 --> 00:18:19,480
Hello?
I saw you looking through the hatch...

267
00:19:03,680 --> 00:19:04,680
(GASPS)

268
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:13,840
How... How can that be me?

269
00:19:19,760 --> 00:19:21,440
(BREATHING DEEPLY)

270
00:19:26,040 --> 00:19:29,960
Who are you? I don't understand,
so just tell me who you are!

271
00:19:40,080 --> 00:19:43,840
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to shoot you.

272
00:19:43,920 --> 00:19:45,600
I'm glad I missed.

273
00:19:46,360 --> 00:19:50,320
But you killed the Doctor.
Or you're...you're going to kill him.

274
00:19:51,600 --> 00:19:53,520
But who are you?

275
00:19:53,600 --> 00:19:56,400
Just please tell me,
because I don't understand!

276
00:19:56,480 --> 00:19:58,000
Please help me.

277
00:19:58,560 --> 00:20:01,520
Help me, please.

278
00:20:10,400 --> 00:20:11,680
(SCREAMS)

279
00:20:12,600 --> 00:20:13,920
(THUMPING)

280
00:20:18,560 --> 00:20:21,680
Oh. It's just some questions.

281
00:20:23,160 --> 00:20:24,520
Yes, I see.

282
00:20:27,680 --> 00:20:30,560
Who was that? Dr Renfrew?

283
00:20:32,880 --> 00:20:34,320
Who was that?

284
00:20:35,480 --> 00:20:36,880
Who was who?

285
00:20:46,040 --> 00:20:49,080
What are you? You can tell me.

286
00:20:50,160 --> 00:20:51,400
'Cause I won't remember.

287
00:20:52,280 --> 00:20:54,800
You invaded us. You're everywhere.

288
00:20:54,880 --> 00:20:59,160
AMY: Help me! Please.
Canton, please, will you help me!

289
00:20:59,520 --> 00:21:03,040
-Are you armed?
-This world is ours.

290
00:21:03,120 --> 00:21:06,960
We have ruled it
since the wheel and the fire.

291
00:21:07,040 --> 00:21:10,600
-We have no need of weapons.
-Yeah?

292
00:21:14,480 --> 00:21:15,920
Welcome to America.

293
00:21:16,280 --> 00:21:17,480
Amy!

294
00:21:18,480 --> 00:21:21,840
You have to tape everything
that happens in this office, every word.

295
00:21:21,920 --> 00:21:23,360
Or we won't know
if you're under the influence.

296
00:21:23,440 --> 00:21:25,560
Doctor, you have to give me
more than this.

297
00:21:25,640 --> 00:21:27,840
-What were you doing to Apollo 777
-A thing. A clever thing.

298
00:21:27,920 --> 00:21:31,560
Now, no more questions.
You have to trust me and nobody else.

299
00:21:32,320 --> 00:21:34,080
Doctor! It's Canton!

300
00:21:34,960 --> 00:21:36,680
Quick, he needs us!

301
00:21:41,800 --> 00:21:45,600
AMY: Help me! Please, I can't...
I can't see! Somebody help me!

302
00:21:45,680 --> 00:21:46,840
Amy!

303
00:21:47,840 --> 00:21:49,640
Amy, can you hear me?

304
00:21:50,240 --> 00:21:54,040
Amy, I'm going to try to blow the lock.
I need you to stand back.

305
00:21:54,480 --> 00:21:57,200
-Okay, gun down, I've got it!
-Amy, we're here. Are you okay?

306
00:21:57,280 --> 00:22:00,720
AMY: I can't see! (SOBBING)

307
00:22:06,720 --> 00:22:08,320
Where is she, Doctor?

308
00:22:14,400 --> 00:22:17,640
-It's empty.
-AMY: It's dark, so dark.

309
00:22:18,320 --> 00:22:22,040
I don't know where I am.
(SOBBING) Please, can anybody hear me?

310
00:22:28,920 --> 00:22:30,920
They took this out of her.

311
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:33,120
How did they do that, Doctor?

312
00:22:33,200 --> 00:22:34,480
(AMY SOBBING)

313
00:22:35,720 --> 00:22:37,840
And, and... Why can I still hear her?

314
00:22:39,640 --> 00:22:41,320
Is it a recording?

315
00:22:45,240 --> 00:22:48,000
Um, it defaults to live.
This is current.

316
00:22:50,120 --> 00:22:52,240
Wherever she is right now,
this is what she's saying.

317
00:22:52,320 --> 00:22:54,280
Amy, can you hear me?
We're coming for you.

318
00:22:55,320 --> 00:22:57,400
Wherever you are, we're coming, I swear.

319
00:22:57,480 --> 00:22:59,120
She can't hear you.

320
00:23:00,640 --> 00:23:02,720
I'm so sorry. It's one-way.

321
00:23:03,720 --> 00:23:06,000
She can always hear me, Doctor.

322
00:23:06,760 --> 00:23:09,240
Always, wherever she is.

323
00:23:09,320 --> 00:23:12,640
And she always knows that I am coming
for her, do you understand me?

324
00:23:14,840 --> 00:23:16,040
Always.

325
00:23:17,920 --> 00:23:20,280
AMY: Doctor, are you out there?

326
00:23:21,280 --> 00:23:24,320
Can you hear me? Doctor?

327
00:23:26,200 --> 00:23:31,360
Oh, God. Please, please, Doctor,
Just get me out of this.

328
00:23:31,760 --> 00:23:34,160
He's coming. I'll bring him, I swear.

329
00:23:35,160 --> 00:23:38,920
Hello, is somebody there? Who...

330
00:23:39,680 --> 00:23:42,440
I, I think someone has been shot.

331
00:23:42,520 --> 00:23:45,080
I think we should help. We...

332
00:23:47,840 --> 00:23:50,360
I can't... I can't remember.

333
00:24:02,840 --> 00:24:03,960
Okay.

334
00:24:06,040 --> 00:24:08,000
Who and what are you?

335
00:24:08,080 --> 00:24:11,560
Silence, Doctor.

336
00:24:13,320 --> 00:24:16,760
We are the Silence.

337
00:24:17,960 --> 00:24:19,880
Silence, Doctor.

338
00:24:19,960 --> 00:24:21,160
-Rory, listen to that.
-Silence?

339
00:24:21,240 --> 00:24:23,400
-We ran from the Silence?
-Silence.

340
00:24:23,480 --> 00:24:27,160
And Silence will fall.

341
00:24:44,960 --> 00:24:48,040
-Hello, again.
-Sir, you've been in there for days.

342
00:24:48,120 --> 00:24:50,600
-What the hell have you been doing?
-Doesn't matter.

343
00:24:50,680 --> 00:24:51,960
I need Dr Shepherd here right now.

344
00:24:52,040 --> 00:24:54,320
Sir, I need to talk to Colonel Jefferson
right now.

345
00:24:54,400 --> 00:24:56,360
No, you really don't.

346
00:25:00,920 --> 00:25:02,280
Uh...

347
00:25:03,680 --> 00:25:04,680
Hi, fellas.

348
00:25:07,840 --> 00:25:10,000
I'm President Nixon.

349
00:25:10,480 --> 00:25:13,000
I want to tell you,
on behalf of the American people,

350
00:25:13,080 --> 00:25:15,320
how much we appreciate
all of your hard work.

351
00:25:15,840 --> 00:25:17,920
MISSION CONTROL: 7he target
for the Apollo 11 astronauts,

352
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:24,040
the moon, at liftoff. will be
at a distance of 218,096 miles away.

353
00:25:24,120 --> 00:25:26,480
We're just past
the two-minute mark on the countdown.

354
00:25:26,560 --> 00:25:29,760
T minus one minute 54 seconds
and counting.

355
00:25:29,840 --> 00:25:31,520
Our status board indicates...

356
00:25:31,600 --> 00:25:34,600
It's an exo-skeleton.
Basically, life support.

357
00:25:35,080 --> 00:25:38,760
There's about 20 different kinds
of alien tech in here.

358
00:25:39,320 --> 00:25:41,560
Who was she? Why put her in here?

359
00:25:41,640 --> 00:25:43,480
Put this on,
you don't even need to eat.

360
00:25:44,120 --> 00:25:47,640
The suit processes sunlight directly.
It's got built-in weaponry

361
00:25:47,720 --> 00:25:50,200
and a communications system
that can hack into anything.

362
00:25:50,280 --> 00:25:51,840
Including the telephone network?

363
00:25:51,920 --> 00:25:53,960
-Easily.
-But why phone the President?

364
00:25:54,040 --> 00:25:56,560
It defaults to the highest authority
it can find.

365
00:25:56,640 --> 00:25:57,920
The little girl gets frightened,

366
00:25:58,000 --> 00:26:00,400
the most powerful man on Earth
gets a phone call.

367
00:26:01,000 --> 00:26:03,920
The night terrors
with a hotline to the White House.

368
00:26:07,160 --> 00:26:09,240
You won't learn anything
from that envelope, you know.

369
00:26:09,320 --> 00:26:12,600
Purchased on Earth, perfectly
ordinary stationery, Tardis blue.

370
00:26:12,680 --> 00:26:15,240
Summoned by a stranger
who won't even show his face.

371
00:26:15,320 --> 00:26:17,160
That's a first for me. How about you?

372
00:26:20,200 --> 00:26:21,960
Our lives are back to front.

373
00:26:22,040 --> 00:26:24,880
Your future's my past,
your firsts are my lasts.

374
00:26:24,960 --> 00:26:27,320
-Not really what I asked.
-Ask something else, then.

375
00:26:27,400 --> 00:26:29,240
What are the Silence doing?
Raising a child?

376
00:26:29,320 --> 00:26:31,400
Keeping her safe.
Even giving her independence.

377
00:26:31,480 --> 00:26:33,720
The only way to save Amy is to work out
what the Silence are doing.

378
00:26:33,800 --> 00:26:35,840
-I know.
-Every single thing we learn about them

379
00:26:35,920 --> 00:26:39,240
-brings us a step closer.
-Yeah, Doctor, I get it, I know.

380
00:26:39,320 --> 00:26:41,680
Of course, it's possible
she's not just any little girl.

381
00:26:41,760 --> 00:26:45,000
Well, I'd say she's human,
going by the life support software.

382
00:26:45,080 --> 00:26:47,560
-But?
-She climbed out of this suit.

383
00:26:48,320 --> 00:26:52,000
Like, she forced her way out.
She must be incredibly strong.

384
00:26:52,080 --> 00:26:54,720
Incredibly strong and running away.
I like her.

385
00:26:54,800 --> 00:26:58,160
-We should be trying to find her.
-Yes, I know, but how?

386
00:26:58,240 --> 00:27:00,240
Anyway, I have the strangest feeling
she's going to find us.

387
00:27:00,320 --> 00:27:03,280
MISSION CONTROL: Apollo 11,
this is Houston, do you read? Over.

388
00:27:03,360 --> 00:27:04,600
(WHITE NOISE)

389
00:27:05,120 --> 00:27:07,360
Why does it look like a NASA space suit?

390
00:27:07,440 --> 00:27:09,920
Because that's what the Silence do.
Think about it.

391
00:27:10,000 --> 00:27:11,560
They don't make anything themselves.

392
00:27:11,640 --> 00:27:14,040
They don't have to. They get
other life forms to do it for them.

393
00:27:14,120 --> 00:27:15,960
-So they're parasites, then?
-Super parasites.

394
00:27:16,080 --> 00:27:18,440
Standing in the shadows of human history
since the very beginning.

395
00:27:18,520 --> 00:27:20,800
We know they can influence
human behaviour any way they want.

396
00:27:20,880 --> 00:27:23,960
If they've been doing that on
a global scale for thousands of years...

397
00:27:24,040 --> 00:27:25,480
Then what?

398
00:27:25,960 --> 00:27:28,920
Then why did the human race
suddenly decide to go to the moon?

399
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:30,960
Ten, nine,

400
00:27:31,040 --> 00:27:35,400
ignition sequence start,
six, five four...

401
00:27:35,480 --> 00:27:38,080
Because the Silence needed a space suit.

402
00:27:38,160 --> 00:27:41,960
MISSION CONTROL: ...one, zero,
all engines firing.

403
00:27:42,040 --> 00:27:44,120
Liftoff. We have a liftoff.

404
00:27:44,200 --> 00:27:48,000
Thirty-two minutes past the hour,
liftoff on Apollo 11.

405
00:27:54,120 --> 00:27:55,840
My God!

406
00:27:57,440 --> 00:28:00,080
-What is it?
-It's just an alien, Dr Shepherd.

407
00:28:00,160 --> 00:28:04,440
-Someone's already been treating it.
-Yeah. You've been treating it.

408
00:28:04,520 --> 00:28:06,760
Does Colonel Jefferson know
this thing is here?

409
00:28:06,840 --> 00:28:10,600
-No.
-Then I'm going to tell him right now!

410
00:28:10,680 --> 00:28:13,760
-Again?
-Sorry, what?

411
00:28:14,720 --> 00:28:15,960
Exactly.

412
00:28:16,480 --> 00:28:19,400
Sergeant, why was I called in here
for no reason?

413
00:28:20,360 --> 00:28:23,400
You tend to my wounds.

414
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:26,240
You are foolish.

415
00:28:26,920 --> 00:28:29,840
Why? What would you do in my place?

416
00:28:29,920 --> 00:28:34,920
We have ruled your lives
since your lives began.

417
00:28:35,000 --> 00:28:37,800
You should kill us all on sight,

418
00:28:37,880 --> 00:28:42,240
but you will never remember
we were even here.

419
00:28:42,600 --> 00:28:45,000
Your will is ours.

420
00:28:45,080 --> 00:28:49,920
Yeah, well, sorry to disappoint you,
but thanks.

421
00:28:50,000 --> 00:28:51,920
It's exactly what I needed to hear.

422
00:28:52,600 --> 00:28:56,400
This is a video phone.
Whatever a video phone is.

423
00:29:03,440 --> 00:29:06,320
You should kill us all on sight.

424
00:29:06,560 --> 00:29:07,920
(AMY SOBBING)

425
00:29:14,680 --> 00:29:18,720
This suit, it seems to be
repairing itself. How is it doing that?

426
00:29:18,800 --> 00:29:20,840
Doctor, a unit like this,

427
00:29:20,920 --> 00:29:23,920
would it ever be able to move
without an occupant?

428
00:29:24,000 --> 00:29:25,760
-Why?
-Well, the little girl said

429
00:29:25,840 --> 00:29:28,360
the spaceman was coming to eat her.

430
00:29:28,840 --> 00:29:30,480
Maybe that's exactly what happened.

431
00:29:32,840 --> 00:29:34,480
AMY: I love you.

432
00:29:35,320 --> 00:29:36,840
I know you think it's him.

433
00:29:37,680 --> 00:29:42,840
I know you think it ought to be him.
But it's not, it's you.

434
00:29:44,040 --> 00:29:45,240
And when I see you again

435
00:29:45,320 --> 00:29:50,400
I'm going to tell you properly,
Just to see your stupid face.

436
00:29:51,200 --> 00:29:56,600
My life was so boring before you
Just dropped out of the sky.

437
00:29:57,400 --> 00:30:01,280
So just get your stupid
face where I can see it. Okay?

438
00:30:02,280 --> 00:30:05,560
Okay? (SOBBING)

439
00:30:06,760 --> 00:30:10,920
She'll be safe for now.
No point in a dead hostage.

440
00:30:13,880 --> 00:30:15,600
Can't you save her?

441
00:30:16,120 --> 00:30:17,960
I can track that signal back.
Take us right to her.

442
00:30:18,040 --> 00:30:20,200
-Then why haven't you?
-Because then what?

443
00:30:20,840 --> 00:30:22,240
I find her and then what do I do?

444
00:30:22,320 --> 00:30:24,600
This isn't an alien invasion,
they live here.

445
00:30:24,680 --> 00:30:27,520
This is their empire.

446
00:30:27,600 --> 00:30:30,160
This is kicking the Romans out of Rome.

447
00:30:31,600 --> 00:30:32,600
Rome fell.

448
00:30:33,480 --> 00:30:35,720
I know. I was there.

449
00:30:38,360 --> 00:30:39,640
So was I.

450
00:30:42,240 --> 00:30:43,920
Personal question.

451
00:30:44,040 --> 00:30:46,000
Seriously, you?

452
00:30:51,240 --> 00:30:53,200
Do you ever remember it?

453
00:30:53,560 --> 00:30:55,760
2,000 years, waiting for Amy?

454
00:30:57,040 --> 00:30:58,760
The Last Centurion?

455
00:31:02,200 --> 00:31:04,000
-No.
-Are you lying?

456
00:31:05,600 --> 00:31:07,880
-Course I'm lying.
-Course you are.

457
00:31:07,960 --> 00:31:10,520
Not the sort of thing anyone forgets.

458
00:31:10,600 --> 00:31:13,120
But I don't remember it all the time.

459
00:31:14,960 --> 00:31:18,320
It's like there's a door in my head.

460
00:31:18,400 --> 00:31:20,920
-(AMY SOBBING)
-I can keep it shut.

461
00:31:21,000 --> 00:31:23,840
Please, please, please come and get me.

462
00:31:24,960 --> 00:31:27,000
Come and get me. (SOBBING)

463
00:31:30,720 --> 00:31:32,840
Okay, all flight controllers,
GO/NO-GO for landing?

464
00:31:32,920 --> 00:31:37,520
NEWSCASTER: Just five days since
Apollo 11 blasted off from Cape Kennedy,

465
00:31:37,600 --> 00:31:41,960
this unprecedented journey
is reaching its crucial moment.

466
00:31:42,040 --> 00:31:44,440
Armstrong and Aldrin
are making their descent

467
00:31:44,520 --> 00:31:46,080
to the surface of the moon.

468
00:31:46,160 --> 00:31:47,200
MISSION CONTROL: ...on the ground.

469
00:31:47,280 --> 00:31:49,440
You got a bunch of guys
about to turn blue.

470
00:32:01,680 --> 00:32:04,000
Where am I? Where is this?

471
00:32:08,480 --> 00:32:10,000
(CHITTERING)

472
00:32:10,080 --> 00:32:12,440
You are Amelia Pond.

473
00:32:14,000 --> 00:32:16,120
You're ugly,
has anyone mentioned that to you?

474
00:32:16,200 --> 00:32:18,960
We do you honour.

475
00:32:19,040 --> 00:32:23,000
You will bring the Silence.

476
00:32:23,480 --> 00:32:26,120
But your part will soon be over.

477
00:32:26,200 --> 00:32:28,640
Whatever that means, you've made
a big mistake bringing me here,

478
00:32:28,720 --> 00:32:31,520
"cause wait till you see
what's coming for you now.

479
00:32:31,600 --> 00:32:35,160
You have been here many days.

480
00:32:35,240 --> 00:32:38,200
No. I just got here.
You just put me in here.

481
00:32:38,280 --> 00:32:42,560
Your memory is weak.
You have been here many days.

482
00:32:42,640 --> 00:32:44,960
No. No, I can't have been.

483
00:32:46,080 --> 00:32:48,720
You will sleep now.

484
00:32:50,200 --> 00:32:51,520
Sleep.

485
00:32:51,640 --> 00:32:54,000
-No! No! Get off me!
-Sleep.

486
00:32:54,080 --> 00:32:56,720
-No! No! No!
-Sleep.

487
00:32:57,800 --> 00:32:59,600
(WHOOSHING)

488
00:33:03,080 --> 00:33:04,840
Oh! Interesting.

489
00:33:05,680 --> 00:33:08,600
Very Aickman Road,
I've seen one of these before.

490
00:33:08,680 --> 00:33:11,080
Abandoned. Wonder how that happened?

491
00:33:11,160 --> 00:33:12,720
Oh, well!
I suppose I'm about to find out.

492
00:33:12,800 --> 00:33:16,320
Rory, River,
keep one Silent in eye shot at all times.

493
00:33:16,400 --> 00:33:18,680
Oh, hello, sorry.
You're in the middle of something.

494
00:33:18,760 --> 00:33:21,120
Just had to say, though,
have you seen what's on the telly?

495
00:33:21,200 --> 00:33:24,040
Oh, hello, Amy, you all right?
Want to watch some television?

496
00:33:24,120 --> 00:33:26,400
Ah, now, stay where you are.

497
00:33:27,960 --> 00:33:29,400
'Cause look at me, I'm confident.

498
00:33:30,120 --> 00:33:32,840
You want to watch that, me,
when I'm confident.

499
00:33:32,920 --> 00:33:34,000
Oh, and this is my friend River.

500
00:33:34,080 --> 00:33:35,960
Nice hair, clever, has her own gun,

501
00:33:36,040 --> 00:33:39,280
and unlike me, she really doesn't mind
shooting people. I shouldn't like that

502
00:33:39,360 --> 00:33:41,120
-but I kind of do a bit.
-Thank you, sweetie.

503
00:33:41,200 --> 00:33:42,680
I know you're team players
and everything,

504
00:33:42,760 --> 00:33:44,880
but she'll definitely kill
at least the first three of you.

505
00:33:44,960 --> 00:33:47,040
-Well, the first seven, easily.
-Seven, really?

506
00:33:47,120 --> 00:33:49,040
-Oh, eight for you, honey.
-Stop it.

507
00:33:49,120 --> 00:33:51,160
-Make me!
-Yeah, well, maybe I will.

508
00:33:51,240 --> 00:33:52,560
Is this really important, flirting?

509
00:33:52,640 --> 00:33:54,480
'Cause I feel like I should be
higher on the list right now.

510
00:33:54,560 --> 00:33:55,640
Yes, right. Sorry.

511
00:33:55,720 --> 00:33:57,440
As I was saying, my naughty friend here

512
00:33:57,520 --> 00:34:00,120
is going to kill the first three of you
to attack, plus him behind.

513
00:34:00,200 --> 00:34:02,600
So maybe you want to draw lots
or have a quiz.

514
00:34:02,680 --> 00:34:04,760
-What's he got?
-Something, I hope.

515
00:34:04,840 --> 00:34:06,160
Or maybe
you could just listen a minute,

516
00:34:06,240 --> 00:34:09,160
because all I really want to do
is accept your total surrender

517
00:34:09,240 --> 00:34:11,560
and then I'll let you go in peace. Yes.

518
00:34:11,640 --> 00:34:14,080
You've been interfering in human
history for thousands of years. Yes.

519
00:34:14,160 --> 00:34:17,400
People have suffered and died.
But what's the point in two hearts

520
00:34:17,480 --> 00:34:19,760
if you can't be a bit forgiving
now and then?

521
00:34:20,440 --> 00:34:22,840
Ooh! The Silence.

522
00:34:23,240 --> 00:34:26,880
You guys take that seriously, don't you?
Okay, you got me, I'm lying.

523
00:34:26,960 --> 00:34:28,280
I'm not really going to let you go
that easily.

524
00:34:28,360 --> 00:34:32,520
Nice thought, but it's not Christmas.
First, you tell me about the girl.

525
00:34:32,600 --> 00:34:35,800
Who is she? Why is she important?
What's she for?

526
00:34:37,000 --> 00:34:39,240
Yeah, we're getting
a picture of it here.

527
00:34:40,560 --> 00:34:42,960
Guys, sorry,

528
00:34:43,040 --> 00:34:45,120
but you're way out of time.

529
00:34:45,200 --> 00:34:47,040
Now, come on, a bit of history for you.

530
00:34:47,120 --> 00:34:50,080
Aren't you proud? Because you helped.

531
00:34:50,160 --> 00:34:53,400
Now, do you know how many people
are watching this live on the telly?

532
00:34:53,480 --> 00:34:56,320
Half a billion, and that's nothing,
"cause the human race

533
00:34:56,400 --> 00:34:58,680
will spread out among the stars,
you just watch them fly.

534
00:34:58,760 --> 00:35:02,080
Billions and billions of them,
for billions and billions of years.

535
00:35:02,160 --> 00:35:04,520
And every single one of them
at some point in their lives

536
00:35:04,600 --> 00:35:07,920
will look back at this man,
taking that very first step,

537
00:35:08,000 --> 00:35:10,880
and they will never, ever forget it.

538
00:35:11,680 --> 00:35:14,440
ALDRIN: Okay. Engine stopped.
ACA out of detent.

539
00:35:15,400 --> 00:35:17,840
Descent Engine Command Override, off.

540
00:35:17,920 --> 00:35:20,720
Oh. But they'll forget this bit.

541
00:35:22,880 --> 00:35:24,320
-Ready?
-Ready.

542
00:35:26,440 --> 00:35:27,920
(SIGNAL WARBLING)

543
00:35:28,440 --> 00:35:29,920
(BEEPING)

544
00:35:31,280 --> 00:35:33,840
ARMSTRONG: It's one small step
for man...

545
00:35:33,920 --> 00:35:36,920
SILENCE: You should kill us all
on sight.

546
00:35:39,600 --> 00:35:42,520
You should kill us all on sight.

547
00:35:44,840 --> 00:35:47,480
You should kill us all on sight.

548
00:35:49,160 --> 00:35:51,840
You should kill us all on sight.

549
00:35:51,920 --> 00:35:54,560
You've given the order
for your own execution,

550
00:35:54,640 --> 00:35:57,000
and the whole planet just heard you.

551
00:35:57,960 --> 00:36:00,840
You should kill us all on sight.

552
00:36:00,920 --> 00:36:03,840
ARMSTRONG: ...one giant leap
for mankind.

553
00:36:03,920 --> 00:36:08,200
And one whacking great
kick up the backside for the Silence!

554
00:36:08,520 --> 00:36:11,560
You just raised an army
against yourself.

555
00:36:11,640 --> 00:36:14,200
And now, for a thousand generations,

556
00:36:14,280 --> 00:36:17,640
you're going to be ordering
them to destroy you every day.

557
00:36:17,720 --> 00:36:19,520
How fast can you run?

558
00:36:19,600 --> 00:36:22,760
'Cause today's the day the human race
throw you off their planet.

559
00:36:22,840 --> 00:36:25,080
They won't even know they're doing it.

560
00:36:25,160 --> 00:36:28,320
I think quite possibly the word
you're looking for right now is,

561
00:36:28,400 --> 00:36:32,440
"Oops!" Run! Guys, I mean us. Run!

562
00:36:34,280 --> 00:36:36,280
(GUNS FIRING)

563
00:36:38,880 --> 00:36:41,000
-I can't get her out!
-Go, just go!

564
00:36:41,080 --> 00:36:42,880
We are not leaving without you!

565
00:36:42,960 --> 00:36:45,960
Will you just get your stupid face
out of here!

566
00:36:49,560 --> 00:36:52,040
Run! Into the Tardis, quickly!

567
00:37:07,040 --> 00:37:08,480
Don't let them build to full power!

568
00:37:08,560 --> 00:37:11,720
I know! There's a reason why
I'm shooting, honey!

569
00:37:13,480 --> 00:37:15,440
-What are you doing?
-Helping.

570
00:37:15,520 --> 00:37:18,040
You've got a screwdriver.
Go build a cabinet!

571
00:37:18,120 --> 00:37:20,840
-That's really rude!
-Shut up and drive!

572
00:37:36,400 --> 00:37:37,720
(GUN POWERS DOWN)

573
00:37:44,440 --> 00:37:49,040
My old fella didn't see that, did he?
He gets ever so cross.

574
00:37:50,680 --> 00:37:54,960
-So, what kind of doctor are you?
-Archaeology.

575
00:37:59,360 --> 00:38:00,760
Love a tomb.

576
00:38:05,040 --> 00:38:06,760
You can let me fly it!

577
00:38:06,840 --> 00:38:09,200
Yeah, or we could go
where we're supposed to.

578
00:38:10,120 --> 00:38:12,760
-What's the matter with you?
-You called me stupid.

579
00:38:12,840 --> 00:38:15,840
-I always call you stupid.
-No, but...

580
00:38:16,840 --> 00:38:18,080
My face.

581
00:38:27,720 --> 00:38:29,360
I wasn't sure who you
were talking about.

582
00:38:29,440 --> 00:38:32,920
-You know, me or...
-Him?

583
00:38:33,600 --> 00:38:34,960
Well, you did say
"dropped out of the sky".

584
00:38:35,040 --> 00:38:37,400
It's a figure of speech, moron!

585
00:38:46,560 --> 00:38:48,680
-Thanks.
-You're welcome.

586
00:38:51,040 --> 00:38:53,920
(CHUCKLES) So we're safe again.

587
00:38:54,000 --> 00:38:56,240
Safe? No, of course you're not safe.

588
00:38:56,320 --> 00:38:57,760
There's about a billion other things
out there

589
00:38:57,840 --> 00:38:59,400
just waiting to burn your whole world.

590
00:38:59,480 --> 00:39:01,440
But if you want to pretend you're safe

591
00:39:01,520 --> 00:39:04,280
just so you can sleep at night,
okay, you're safe.

592
00:39:04,360 --> 00:39:06,200
But you're not really.

593
00:39:06,520 --> 00:39:09,720
-Canton. Till the next one, eh?
-Looking forward to it.

594
00:39:09,800 --> 00:39:12,200
Canton just wants to get married.

595
00:39:12,600 --> 00:39:14,480
Helluva reason
to kick him out of the FBI.

596
00:39:14,560 --> 00:39:16,160
I'm sure something can be arranged.

597
00:39:16,240 --> 00:39:18,680
-I'm counting on you.
-Er, Doctor...

598
00:39:20,080 --> 00:39:22,400
Canton here tells me you're...

599
00:39:24,280 --> 00:39:25,960
You're from the future.

600
00:39:26,800 --> 00:39:29,160
Hardly seems possible,
but I was wondering...

601
00:39:29,240 --> 00:39:31,160
Should warn you.
I don't answer a lot of questions.

602
00:39:31,240 --> 00:39:34,400
But I'm a president
at the beginning of his time.

603
00:39:35,960 --> 00:39:37,320
Dare I ask?

604
00:39:38,120 --> 00:39:39,920
Will I be remembered?

605
00:39:40,520 --> 00:39:42,560
Oh, Dicky. Tricky Dicky.

606
00:39:43,840 --> 00:39:46,280
They're never going to forget you.

607
00:39:47,960 --> 00:39:50,240
-Say hi to David Frost for me.
-David Frost?

608
00:39:54,200 --> 00:39:56,680
This person you want to marry.

609
00:39:56,760 --> 00:39:59,720
-Black?
-Yes...

610
00:40:00,400 --> 00:40:03,680
I know what people think of me,
but perhaps I'm a little more liberal...

611
00:40:03,760 --> 00:40:04,920
...he is.

612
00:40:08,200 --> 00:40:12,720
I think the moon is far enough
for now, don't you, Mr Delaware?

613
00:40:12,800 --> 00:40:14,640
I figured it might be.

614
00:40:17,000 --> 00:40:18,000
(EXHALES)

615
00:40:18,120 --> 00:40:21,800
-You could come with us.
-I escape often enough, thank you.

616
00:40:22,840 --> 00:40:25,320
And I have a promise to live up to.

617
00:40:27,400 --> 00:40:29,080
You'll understand soon enough.

618
00:40:29,480 --> 00:40:32,040
Okay, up to you.

619
00:40:33,200 --> 00:40:37,080
-See you next time. Call me.
-What, that's it?

620
00:40:37,160 --> 00:40:41,320
-(CHUCKLES) What's the matter with you?
-Have I forgotten something?

621
00:40:42,600 --> 00:40:45,160
Oh, shut up.

622
00:41:00,200 --> 00:41:03,960
Right. Okay. Interesting.

623
00:41:05,840 --> 00:41:07,200
What's wrong?

624
00:41:07,280 --> 00:41:08,840
You're acting like
we've never done that before.

625
00:41:08,920 --> 00:41:10,280
We haven't.

626
00:41:12,520 --> 00:41:14,560
-We haven't?
-Oh, look at the time, must be off.

627
00:41:14,640 --> 00:41:18,120
Um, but it was very nice.
It was... It was good.

628
00:41:18,200 --> 00:41:20,600
It was unexpected.

629
00:41:24,240 --> 00:41:28,000
You know what they say,
there's a first time for everything.

630
00:41:31,560 --> 00:41:33,160
And a last time.

631
00:41:35,280 --> 00:41:37,080
Rory, I'm going to need
thermo couplings.

632
00:41:37,160 --> 00:41:40,360
-The green ones and the blue ones.
-Okay, hold on.

633
00:41:44,440 --> 00:41:46,280
-So.
-So.

634
00:41:46,360 --> 00:41:50,840
-You're okay?
-Fine. Head's a bit weird.

635
00:41:51,480 --> 00:41:54,360
There's lots of stuff
I can't quite remember.

636
00:42:00,880 --> 00:42:03,000
After-effect of the Silence.
Natural enough.

637
00:42:03,080 --> 00:42:06,840
That's not what I was asking.
You told me you were pregnant.

638
00:42:07,640 --> 00:42:09,240
-Yes.
-Why?

639
00:42:09,320 --> 00:42:13,440
Because I was. I mean, I...
I thought I was. Turns out I wasn't.

640
00:42:13,520 --> 00:42:16,760
-No. Why did you tell me?
-Because you're my friend.

641
00:42:18,400 --> 00:42:20,240
You're my best friend.

642
00:42:22,600 --> 00:42:24,520
Hmm. Did you tell Rory?

643
00:42:28,360 --> 00:42:29,400
AMY: No.

644
00:42:30,560 --> 00:42:32,200
DOCTOR: Amy,
why tell me and not Rory?

645
00:42:32,280 --> 00:42:34,560
-Why do you think?
-I don't know.

646
00:42:35,480 --> 00:42:38,600
I travelled with you in this Tardis
for so long.

647
00:42:38,680 --> 00:42:40,160
All that time.

648
00:42:41,160 --> 00:42:44,560
If I was pregnant for some of it,
wouldn't it have had an effect?

649
00:42:44,640 --> 00:42:47,160
Because I don't want to tell Rory
his baby might have three heads

650
00:42:47,280 --> 00:42:49,680
or like a time head or something.

651
00:42:50,560 --> 00:42:53,000
-What's a time head?
-I don't know, but what if it had one?

652
00:42:53,080 --> 00:42:56,160
-A time head?
-Shut up, all right?

653
00:42:56,240 --> 00:42:57,960
(BOTH LAUGHING)

654
00:42:58,040 --> 00:42:59,640
AMY: Oi, stupid face!

655
00:43:03,480 --> 00:43:04,960
Uh, yeah?

656
00:43:07,480 --> 00:43:08,480
Hello.

657
00:43:08,560 --> 00:43:11,120
I'm taking that away from you if
you're going to listen in all the time.

658
00:43:11,200 --> 00:43:13,160
Okay, that's... That's a fair point.

659
00:43:13,280 --> 00:43:15,520
But you should've told me
that you thought you were pregnant.

660
00:43:16,600 --> 00:43:19,000
I'm a nurse, I'm good with pregnancy.

661
00:43:19,080 --> 00:43:21,600
Not, as it turns out, that good.

662
00:43:21,680 --> 00:43:24,120
-So can you stop being stupid?
-Er, no.

663
00:43:24,200 --> 00:43:26,440
Never. I'm never,
ever going to stop being stupid!

664
00:43:26,520 --> 00:43:30,400
So, this little girl,
it's all about her. Who was she?

665
00:43:31,560 --> 00:43:33,240
Or we could just go off
and have some adventures.

666
00:43:33,320 --> 00:43:36,720
Anyone in the mood for adventures?
"Cause I am. You only live once.

667
00:43:53,040 --> 00:43:54,040
(SCANNER BEEPS)

668
00:43:55,480 --> 00:43:58,240
(SIREN WAILING, HORNS HONKING)

669
00:44:13,400 --> 00:44:14,760
(GIRL COUGHS)

670
00:44:17,520 --> 00:44:18,880
Are you okay?

671
00:44:19,920 --> 00:44:22,040
-Little girl...
-(GIRL COUGHING)

672
00:44:22,120 --> 00:44:24,200
-Are you okay?
-It's all right.

673
00:44:25,520 --> 00:44:27,320
It's quite all right.

674
00:44:27,800 --> 00:44:32,120
I'm dying, but I can fix that.

675
00:44:33,120 --> 00:44:36,800
It's easy, really. See?

676
00:45:01,400 --> 00:45:02,400
Yo ho ho!

677
00:45:02,680 --> 00:45:04,920
Our sensors picked you up.
Ship in distress.

678
00:45:05,000 --> 00:45:07,520
It's dangerous here.
There is a monster aboard.

679
00:45:07,600 --> 00:45:09,000
She leaves a mark on men's skin.

680
00:45:09,080 --> 00:45:10,560
Hello, Doctor, what's happening to me?

681
00:45:10,640 --> 00:45:11,640
You're stowaways!

682
00:45:11,880 --> 00:45:14,040
-(LAUGHING)
-Amy, what are you doing?

683
00:45:14,120 --> 00:45:15,720
Saving your life.
Okay with that, are you?

684
00:45:20,560 --> 00:45:23,400
There's a stroppy, homicidal mermaid
trying to kill all.

685
00:45:24,720 --> 00:45:25,720
(SCREECHING)

686
00:45:25,800 --> 00:45:26,920
(AMY SCREAMING)

687
00:45:27,320 --> 00:45:28,320
She's here.

